tion\'s name, mood options, button labels, and even messages for empty states, like \"Aucune activit\303\251 enregistr\303\251e!\". I am prioritizing a natural and accurate translation of terms crucial to the application\'s user experience. I am carefully translating phrases related to the syncing of the application data.\n\n\n**Extending Language Translations**\n\nI\'m now expanding the language translations to French and German, focusing on common phrases and labels. I\'ve translated several phrases, including \"Daily Break Reminder\" to \"Rappel de Pause Journalier\" and \"Daily Break Reminder\" to \"T\303\244gliche Pauserinnerung\". I\'m also including \"Schedule with Google Calendar\" to \"Planifier sur Google Calendar\" and \"Planen mit Google Kalender\". I\'m ensuring all these translations are contextually accurate!\n\n\n**Implementing German Translations**\n\nI am now implementing German translations. I have successfully translated key phrases and labels into German, including \"Save to Database\" to \"Sichern,\" \"Active Checks\" to \"Stimmungsprotokoll,\" \"Health Sync\" to \"Gesundheitssynchronisierung,\" and \"Biometric Security\" to \"Biometrische Sicherheit\". I\'m also addressing \"Language,\" \"Settings & Privacy,\" and other phrases and ensuring accuracy.\n\n\n"
