    thinking: "**Formulating The Description**\n\nThe build is successful, with a green test suite! I\'m now working on the final description, aiming for precise language when conceptualizing the design. My current focus is on adhering to the provided guidelines for the most effective description.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I have built and configured the **MoodFit** Android application, utilizing contemporary Material 3 spacing and Jetpack Compose design patterns. \n\nHere is a conceptual and visual design overview of the implemented features:\n\n*   **Dynamic Atmosphere Theme**: The screen layout features fluid, ambient gradient backgrounds that shift responsively to reflect the current selected state (e.g., energetic amber hues for **Happy**, soothing seafoam greens for **Stressed**, and deep nighttime purples for **Tired**). It supports a synchronized dark mode toggle for comfortable evening wellness sessions.\n*   **Intuitive State Selector**: Built a responsive dual-input mood selection matrix incorporating both a modern grid of tap-to-select chips and a high-fidelity dropdown selector.\n*   **Structured Gemini AI Guidance**: Connects to the robust `gemini-3.5-flash` model via an optimized network client. It commands structured JSON results parsing into discrete wellness recommendations with physical action instructions and duration limits, while automatically fallback-degrading to pre-configured local suggestions when offline.\n*   **Native Calendar & Social Intents**: Integrates directly with the platform\'s calendar providers to automatically seed event timelines with the recommended wellness actions, and includes immediate social content share flows.\n*   **Room Database Offline Persistence**: Persists favorite routines in a local Room database, responsive to swipe insertions and removals, alongside historical user state logs.\n*   **Long-Term Analytics Canvas**: Uses custom native drawing on a Compose Canvas to plot energy levels and mood frequency fluctuations over time.\n*   **OAuth Synchronizer & Biometric Overrides**: Features a fully responsive simulated Google account auth badge and a biometric lock overlay, prompting user security fingerprint checks.\n*   **Custom Notifications & Health Vitals**: Simulates health tracker sensory inputs (such as active Garmin/Fitbit heart rate pulse telemetry) to dynamically tailor suggestions, alongside hourly break settings that trigger real Android system notifications."
    thinking_duration {
      nanos: 229237004
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
