n layout and the rounded corners. I\'m exploring adaptive rounded boxes for the icons, using pastel colors like PastelPink, PastelLilac, or PastelPurple. The idea is to have an emoji inside! I am now trying to match the HTML layout for each individual list item.\n\n\n**Optimizing Activity Card**\n\nI\'m now completely restructuring the `ActivitySuggestionCard` for enhanced visual appeal and functionality, using a column layout for the activity details, description, and action buttons. I\'m focusing on the integration of an emoji-styled icon, dynamically chosen based on activity type, within a translucent, rounded container.  I\'m aiming for clean and cohesive design.\n\n\n**Enhancing Activity Visuals**\n\nI\'m now implementing the dynamic styling for activity cards. I\'m focusing on lines 620-751 in `ExploreTabContent`. I\'m incorporating an emoji-based icon and pastel background color, dynamically chosen using a `when` statement based on activity type. I\'m building each item, including title, description, category tags, and action buttons for easy sharing. The goal is to provide a visually interesting card for each activity.\n\n\n"
