nize the content. I\'m focusing on text elements, using the appropriate text and background colors for both dark and light modes, applying `RoundedCornerShape` and padding for visual style. I\'m implementing the spacing between the text elements within the `Row` using `Arrangement.spacedBy`.\n\n\n**Adding Action Buttons**\n\nI\'m now implementing the \"Schedule\" button, focusing on its visual style. I\'ve defined different container and content colors for both dark and light modes, and implemented rounded corners, applying the necessary padding and ensuring the proper height. The share button will follow a very similar pattern!\n\n\n\n**Finalizing Action Buttons**\n\nI\'ve just added the \"Calendar\" action button, integrating it within the layout. I\'ve used `testTag` for easy testing. The share button is next, also fully styled and implemented. The calendar and share buttons are looking really clean, fully styled, and implemented in the UI.\n\n\n\n**Integrating the Implementation**\n\nI\'m ready to integrate this component into the main application. I\'ve examined the surrounding code within `MainActivity.kt`, specifically lines 615-625, to ensure a seamless replacement of the `ActivitySuggestionCard`. I\'m going to carefully replace the existing component implementation with the new, refined version to ensure no disruption in the application\'s functionality.\n\n\n"
